cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and encoding methods. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of encoding algorithms to improve performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of spatial information and patch-based methods suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and feature extraction, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
